<h3 id="modules">Modules</h3>

<p><a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/views">Views</a></p>

<p><a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/semanticviews">Semantic Views</a></p>

<p>Please download the above modules at their project pages. On a side note, get the recommended versions (usually these are ready for prime time on live sites.) For clarityâ€™s sake, Iâ€™m going to use a tokenÂ <strong>[yourwebsite]</strong>Â as a substitute for your Drupal Websiteâ€™s URL.</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>After installing the modules go to the modules Admin page and enable them.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Visit the Views Admin page at [yourwebsite]<strong>/admin/build/views</strong>. ClickÂ <strong>Add</strong>Â and create a new view ofÂ <strong>View Type: Node</strong>. Click Next.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I hope you have some content on your website, if not you can use theÂ <a href="http://www.drupal.org/project/devel">Devel</a>Â module and auto generate some demo nodes.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Under fields in Views, Click Add to put some fields.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>Choose the fieldsÂ <strong>Node: Body</strong>Â andÂ <strong>Node: Title</strong>. Donâ€™t bother with changing any other settings.</p>

<p>Rearrange the fields so that the Node Title is above the Node Body.</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Now lets use Views Semantics for the styling. On the Viewâ€™s page go and click onÂ <strong>Style: Unformatted</strong>, chooseÂ <strong>Semantic Views</strong>Â from the options that appear. ClickÂ <strong>Update</strong>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>From the settings that appear now, leave everything as is and Click Update again.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Now go and clickÂ <strong>Row Style: Fields</strong>Â link. Change the settings from Fields toÂ <strong>Semantic Views: Fields</strong>. ClickÂ <strong>Update</strong>Â and you will be presented with options to define html tags and CSS class names on fields.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>ClickÂ <strong>Update</strong>Â to save our style settings. Next go right ahead and ClickÂ <strong>Save</strong>. We are done with configuring a very simple View.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Next Up, lets style our View for a slick presentation. Copy the following code to your CSS files of your active theme.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="language-css highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">div</span><span class="nc">.newbodyclass</span><span class="p">{</span>

    <span class="nl">background</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">none</span> <span class="nb">repeat</span> <span class="nb">scroll</span> <span class="m">0</span> <span class="m">0</span> <span class="m">#DDDDDD</span><span class="p">;</span>
    
    <span class="nl">margin</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">12px</span><span class="p">;</span>
    
    <span class="nl">padding</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">6px</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="nt">div</span><span class="nc">.newnodetitle</span><span class="p">{</span>
    
    <span class="nl">border-bottom</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="m">1px</span> <span class="nb">solid</span> <span class="m">#BBBBBB</span><span class="p">;</span>
    
